quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  11,115,"And be patient, for indeed, Allāh does not allow to be lost the reward of those who do good."
  11,116,"So why were there not{1} among the generations before you those of enduring discrimination forbidding corruption on earth - except a few of those We saved from among them? But those who wronged pursued what luxury they were given therein, and they were criminals.",footnotes:1:Meaning "If only there had been..."
  11,117,"And your Lord would not have destroyed the cities unjustly while their people were reformers."
  12,76,"So he began [the search] with their bags before the bag of his brother; then he extracted it from the bag of his brother. Thus did We plan for Joseph. He could not have taken his brother within the religion [i.e., law] of the king except that Allāh willed. We raise in degrees whom We will, but over every possessor of knowledge is one [more] knowing.{1}",footnotes:1:Ending with the ultimate knowledge of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā).
  12,77,"They said, ",footnotes:1:He did not answer that he himself had been stolen by them from his father.
  12,78,"They said, ",footnotes:1:Addressing Joseph, who now held the title of "al-ʿAzeez."
  13,43,"And those who have disbelieved say, ",footnotes:1:i.e., those who recognize the truth through their knowledge of previous scriptures.
  14,22,"And Satan will say when the matter has been concluded, ",footnotes:1:By your obedience to me instead of Him during life on earth.
  14,23,"And those who believed and did righteous deeds will be admitted to gardens beneath which rivers flow, abiding eternally therein by permission of their Lord; and their greeting therein will be, "
  14,24,"Have you not considered how Allāh presents an example, [making] a good word like a good tree, whose root is firmly fixed and its branches [high] in the sky?"